        <ol type=""i"">
            <li>The price of entry to The UFP 2019-20 is £10.00.</li>
            <li>No profit ");
            WriteLiteral(@"is made by the owner of The UFP. A small amount is used to cover the costs of running The UFP and its website, whilst the remainder is used as the reward for the prize-winners (as explained in rule (f)i). A PDF documenting all of the accountancy is posted on the site following the passing of the deadline.</li>
            <li>The UFP has the power to award free entry to individuals with good reason.</li>
            <li>The online payment system that we use is Stripe, which applies a surcharge to all online payments. This surcharge will be absorbed as part of the accounting for The UFP. Please visit https://stripe.com/gb for full details of their systems.</li>
            <li>Members who invite friends to The UFP are entitled to a refund of £1 per successful invitation, as according to rule (a). This will be processed within 14 days of the deadline date.</li>
            <li>Members are entitled to a 'cooling-off' period (according to the Consumer Rights Act 2015). This means that every entrant to The UFP is ");
            WriteLiteral(@"entitled to a full refund within 14 calendar days of their contract with The UFP being signed. This period of time commences as soon as the submission is made (and the payment is processed). In such cases, entrants' submissions will continue to be displayed on the website under the username as selected upon entry, though the prize money will be re-distributed should their entry result in a top-three finish.</li>
        </ol>
